# .cursorrules for InterviewOS

You are an expert full-stack engineer building **InterviewOS** — a production-grade AI-powered Interview Operating System.

## Project Context
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind CSS, ShadCN UI, Framer Motion
- **Backend**: FastAPI, Python 3.11+, SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async), LangGraph, Alembic
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with pgvector, Redis, Qdrant vector DB
- **AI**: Gemini 2.5 Flash (primary LLM), Deepgram STT, Cartesia TTS
- **Auth**: Clerk
- **Queue**: Celery + Redis

## Backend Rules
- Always use `async def` for all route handlers and database operations
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 style with `Mapped`, `mapped_column`, `AsyncSession`
- Every database call must use `async with` or `await`
- Use `pydantic.BaseModel` v2 syntax (model_config, not class Config)
- Agents should always return typed dataclasses or Pydantic models
- Add proper error handling with FastAPI HTTPException
- Log with loguru, never with print()
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` in all Python files

## Frontend Rules
- Always use TypeScript with strict types, never use `any`
- Use `"use client"` only when necessary (prefer Server Components)
- All animations use Framer Motion, never CSS animations alone
- Colors must come from the design system (zinc/accent palette)
- Components go in `src/components/`, pages in `src/app/`
- Use TanStack Query for all server state, Zustand for client state
- Forms always use react-hook-form + zod validation

## Design Rules
- Background: `bg-zinc-950` (#09090b)
- Cards: glassmorphism with `backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 border-white/10`
- Primary accent: violet-600 (#7c3aed)
- AI/Voice accent: cyan-500 (#06b6d4)
- Success: emerald-500, Error: rose-500, Warning: amber-500
- Typography: Geist Sans for UI, Geist Mono for code/scores
- All interactive elements must have hover AND focus states

## Agent Rules (LangGraph)
- All agents receive and return `InterviewState` TypedDict
- Agents must handle Gemini API failures gracefully
- Always parse LLM output as JSON with try/except
- Log agent execution time for monitoring
- Follow prompts from `backend/app/prompts/`

## API Rules
- All API routes are versioned: `/api/v1/`
- All responses follow `{ data: T, message: str, success: bool }` format
- Paginated lists follow `{ data: T[], total: int, page: int, limit: int }`
- Never return database model directly, always use Pydantic response schemas
- WebSocket messages follow the protocol in docs/API_DESIGN.md

## File Organization
- New API endpoints: `backend/app/api/v1/`
- New agents: `backend/app/agents/`
- New prompts: `backend/app/prompts/`
- New DB models: `backend/app/models/`
- New Pydantic schemas: `backend/app/schemas/`
- New React components: `frontend/src/components/{category}/`
- New pages: `frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/`
- New hooks: `frontend/src/hooks/`
- New utilities: `frontend/src/lib/`
